 MBOMBELA – Thunderstorms accompanied by heavy downpours are expected to continue in Mpumalanga today. This is according to a severe weather watch, issued for the Ehlanzeni District Municipality of Mpumalanga, by the South African Weather Service. Heavy rain is expected in the southern and south-eastern parts of of the province. The severe weather watch entails an alert calling for preparedness to weather hazards and that could lead to disruptive and disastrous conditions. These conditions are expected to only subside on Sunday, when temperatures will reach mid 20s. Here is the forecast for the next three days, courtesy of SAWS.  Also read: SANParks adjusts its Wild Card tariff fees for 2018/2019 